147574.name: nitrogen_input
147574.description: Nitrogen inputs are measured as the application of nitrogen to crops either from synthetic fertilizers, or organic sources such as manure.

source.name: Lassaletta, Billen, Grizzetti, Anglade & Garnier (2014). 50 year trends in nitrogen use efficiency of world cropping systems: the relationship between yield and nitrogen input to cropland. Environmental Research Letters.
source.dataPublishedBy: Lassaletta, L., Billen, G., Grizzetti, B., Anglade, J., & Garnier, J. (2014). 50 year trends in nitrogen use efficiency of world cropping systems: the relationship between yield and nitrogen input to cropland. Environmental Research Letters, 9(10), 105011.
source.additionalInfo:
This dataset measures the nitrogen balance of agricultural inputs and outputs.

Nitrogen inputs are measured as the application of nitrogen to crops either from synthetic fertilizers, or organic sources such as manure.

Nitrogen output is measured as the nitrogen produced in the form of crops.

Nitrogen use efficiency (NUE) is the ratio between nitrogen inputs and output. A NUE of 40% means that only 40% of nitrogen inputs are converted into nitrogen in the form of crops. The remaining 60% is lost to the environment as a pollutant.
